  "body": "When use golang rpc client to call rpc api, the response is unmarshalled to the following struct first\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/f951e23fb5ad2f7017f314a95287bc0506a67d05/rpc/client.go#L80-L89\r\nWith `Result  json.RawMessage`, when unmarshal json response with  null result like \r\n```json\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":null}\r\n```\r\nafter unmarshalled to the `jsonrpcMessage` struct, the `Result` filed is requal to `json.RawMessage([]byte(\"null\"))`, not empty byte slice, and then go to the following process logic\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/f951e23fb5ad2f7017f314a95287bc0506a67d05/rpc/client.go#L307-L317\r\nThe following code \r\n```golang\r\ncase len(resp.Result) == 0:\r\n\treturn ErrNoResult\r\n```\r\nwill never triggered and `err`/`resp.Error` are both nil,  so the default switch will be called\r\n```golang\r\ndefault: \r\n \treturn json.Unmarshal(resp.Result, &result) \r\n```\r\nand `resp.Result` is `[]byte(\"null\")`, this will cause unmarshal error like `missing required field 'cumulativeGasUsed' for Receipt` which is misleading. \r\n\r\nIn my opinion, when `{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":null}` rpc response is returned, the `ErrNoResult` error or some other predefined error  should be returned, not unmarshal error.  Unmarshal null result should be avoid !\r\n\r\nMy previous PR https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/pull/17779\r\n\r\n\r\n",
