    "body": "In #17779, you wrote: \r\n\r\n> use rcp client to get transaction receipt on the mainnet node, but, the tx hash is not existed,\r\n> then, I got the error missing required field 'cumulativeGasUsed' for  \r\n> Receipt which is a misleading error message returned by json.Unmarshal\r\n\r\n`rpc.Client` handles `{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"id\": 1, \"result\": null}` correctly. The error `ErrNoResult` is for cases where \"result\" field is **missing** (example: `{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"id\": 1}`). \r\n\r\nAre you using the ethclient package to get the transaction receipt? ethclient handles `null` result by unmarshaling into `**types.Receipt`: \r\n\r\n```go\r\n    var r *types.Receipt                                                                                      \r\n    err := ec.c.CallContext(ctx, &r, \"eth_getTransactionReceipt\", txHash)                                     \r\n    if err == nil && r == nil {                                                                                 \r\n          // receipt not found\r\n    }                                                                                                         \r\n```\r\n",
